title: Iran to impose tougher punishments on women who refuse to wear headscarf
description: Iran has passed a law to impose more severe punishments on women who refuse to wear the mandatory Islamic headscarf in public.

title: Spanish Football Federation secretary general sacked in wake of Rubiales kiss row
description: The secretary general of the Spanish Football Federation has been sacked after it reached a deal with women players who threatened to boycott the national team.

title: No passport required as departures from airport set for 'seamless' travel
description: Travellers departing from one of the world's busiest airports will soon be able to do so without needing a passport.

title: Liam Gallagher adopts dog rescued by Thai animal sanctuary
description: An abandoned puppy has been adopted by former Oasis frontman Liam Gallagher after being saved in a Thailand sanctuary.

title: World's biggest flower that stinks like rotten meat 'at risk of extinction'
description: The world's foulest-smelling flower - which mimics the odour of rotting flesh - could be at risk of extinction.

title: Ceasefire agreed in Nagorno-Karabakh after dozens killed in Azerbaijan military offensive
description: A ceasefire has been agreed in the Nagorno-Karabakh region after dozens died in shelling, according to Azerbaijan and ethnic-Armenian officials.

title: Spain's World Cup-winning women's squad to end team boycott after kiss row
description: Spain's World Cup winning women's squad has agreed to end their boycott of the national team.
